Package com.intel.fightclub.dialog.events

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllRelevantSensorsConnectedEvent
    Code to notify dialog that all relevant sensors are connected upon start of workout.
    AppMessageEvent
    Event to call the user's attention through the CUI.
    AudioChannelEvent
    An event to indicate dialog that the audio channel to the wearable was opened/closed.
    BatteryLevelEvent
    Event to notify dialog about low and critical battery levels on the wearable.
    CoachingCommentaryEvent
    Defines commentary events.
    DeviceErrorEvent
    Event to deal with device errors when starting stopping the workout.
    DialogEvent
    Defines a DialogEvent.
    RelevantSensorsDisconnectedEvent
    Event to notify the user about relevant sensors that are disconnected upon workout start.
    RetryableDialogEvent
    Defines a retryable DialogEvent for which retry attempts will be made if the message cannot be successfully delivered to the DialogManager.
    SensorStatusEvent
    Event to notify about sensor connection/disconnection.
    VerbosityUpdatedEvent
    This event occurs when the verbosity level changes.
    WearableStatusEvent
    Events to notify dialog about wearable connection/disconnection.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AppMessageEvent.AppMessageEventType
    Defines app message event types as understood by the dialogue engine.
    AudioChannelEvent.EventType
    Restricts valid values to indicate the type of event when channel was opened/closed.
    BatteryLevelEvent.BatteryStateClassification
    Defines battery classifications as understood by the dialogue engine.
    DeviceErrorEvent.ErrorType
    Restricts valid values to indicate the error type.
    SensorStatusEvent.EventType
    Restricts valid values to indicate the type of event: Connection/Disconnection.
    WearableStatusEvent.EventType
    Restricts valid values to indicate the type of event: Connection/Disconnection.
